This shoe is new but elder too. Because it is based on the traditional majorcan “porquera”. A humble shoe that was created in the 20’s.

name: The SPF
description:
The SPF effectively protects your skin from UVA and UVB rays with chemical UV filters. Soothing ingredients such as sunflower oil nourish the skin without leaving it greasy. Rosemary extract and ethyl ferulate are natural antioxidants that provide additional protection for skin cells. Our sunscreen is coral compatible. Suitable for sensitive skin.

Key ingredients:

-Rosmarinus Officinalis (Rosemary) Leaf Extract
Radical exposure to sunlight (UV rays) is increasingly being increased by artificial radiation (blue light). Carotenoids form a protective shield against harmful radiation in the skin barrier and act as antioxidants that eliminate free radicals and reduce lipid peroxidation. The skin barrier is strengthened and the skin remains elastic and rejuvenated.

-Ethyl ferulate
Ethyl ferulate is a natural antioxidant extracted from rice. It protects skin cells and their DNA by absorbing UV radiation and neutralising oxygen radicals. We combine it with rosemary extract, which is rich in carnosolic acid. Together they support the skin's defences against free radicals, especially in situations of increased radical stress, such as UV exposure.

-Helianthus Annus (Sunflower) Seed Oil
Sunflower oil contains many good properties for the skin, including oleic acid, vitamin E and linoleic acid. It strengthens the skin's barrier function and supports moisturisation. This oil is super light and absorbs quickly. It is also non-comedogenic, i.e. it does not clog pores.

description:
Our vintage rugs we find in Iran come from used Persian rugs that continue their trip after they have been redesigned and redesigned. In Iran, designers based in Iran recycle old handmade perpeased rugs as raw material for their art.

Each rug is carefully selected and goes through a unique process of washing and color neutralization. In a creative process, parts of the flor are removed or reduced to create a new design. The rug is then recolored in new fascinating colors and patterns. The result is a unique and modern individual work of art. Of course, these vintage rugs are, old and used and the condition is accordingly what is part of the product.

The Gashghai or Qashqai are Turkish -speaking nomad strains, which mainly live in the province of Fars, especially around the city of Shiraz in the southwest of Iran. In addition to rugs, they also produce a wide variety of flat -woven Kelim, which are produced in the typical slot weaving technique. This means that slots in the Kelim are part of the manufacturing process, especially when changing color. The technology implies the structure of the motifs, which are mainly geometrically - typical Kelim patterns. The nomads do not adhere to a given design or a template. They build according to their memory and their personal taste. The result is a wide variety of patterns and colors, which is only based on the individual taste and tradition of the knoters. One advantage of the slit-Kelim technique is that you can use these flat tissue from both sides.
name: Kelim Gashgai 403 x 320

description: Viivakoru pendant: ‘Viivakoru’ is the name of this jewellery series. ‘Viiva’ means “line” in Finnish, and “koru” stands for “jewellery”.
